The project is AGPL-3.0 because its neural CW decoder bundles the DeepCW model, which
is AGPL-3.0. If you run a modified version of this software and let users interact
with it over a network, AGPL section 13 requires you to offer them the corresponding
source. The app links to its source repository in the CW tool's footer.

Bundled / third-party components
--------------------------------
- DeepCW model  -  frontend/models/deepcw/model.onnx + model.onnx.json
    The neural Morse decoder weights, from github.com/e04/deepcw-engine.
    Copyright (C) e04.  Licensed AGPL-3.0-only.
    frontend/cw-worker.js's spectrogram + greedy-CTC steps are adapted from that
    repository's AGPL-3.0 examples (examples/nodejs/decode_morse.mjs).

- ONNX Runtime Web  -  frontend/vendor/ort/
